@vitordelima Yeah I love gasification too!  

Granted for long chain hydrocarbons, HTL may be more efficient, but for many things (Alcohols, Plastics, Some Pharmaceuticals, Propellants/LPG, etc) Gasification and a “Gas to Liquids” or the conventional usage (of ethylene etc) of the chemicals works just fine.

A Hydrogen, Methanol, or my favorite, Dimethyl Ether (DME) based economy could use all sorts of sources including gasification.

